snSwGroupOperMode.name: snSwGroupOperMode
snSwGroupOperMode.description: noVLan(1) represents all switch ports with no virtual LAN by port (no Port VLAN), and with no tag assigned. vlanByPort(2) represents all switch ports with Basic VLAN (layer2 Switch).

snSwGroupIpL3SwMode.name: snSwGroupIpL3SwMode
snSwGroupIpL3SwMode.description: The Switch Group is configured with the Layer3 IP Switch mode either enabled or disabled and the default is disabled mode. enabled(1)...........activate Layer3 IP Switch disabled(0)..........disable Layer3 IP Switch

snSwGroupIpMcastMode.name: snSwGroupIpMcastMode
snSwGroupIpMcastMode.description: The Switch Group is configured with the IP Multicast pruning mode either enabled or disabled and the default is disabled mode. enabled(1)...........activate IP Multicast pruning disabled(0)..........no IP Multicast pruning

snSwGroupDefaultCfgMode.name: snSwGroupDefaultCfgMode
snSwGroupDefaultCfgMode.description: The Switch Group is configured with the Default configuration. If the default configuration gets overwritten, the state will change to non-default. default(1)...........default configuration nonDefault(2)..........non default configuration

snSwGroupSwitchAgeTime.name: snSwGroupSwitchAgeTime
snSwGroupSwitchAgeTime.description: The Switch Age time is 180sec by default. The configured range is 10 to 10,000sec. The time represents the time span to age out an MAC Address entry.

snVLanGroupVlanCurEntry.name: snVLanGroupVlanCurEntry
snVLanGroupVlanCurEntry.description: The current total entry number of VLANs are configured.

snVLanGroupSetAllVLan.name: snVLanGroupSetAllVLan
snVLanGroupSetAllVLan.description: The value of this object is the VLanIndex of a particalur entry in snVLanByPortTable (snVLanByPortVLanIndex). All the attributes of that row of table except PortMask will be used to set the same attributes for the entire VLan group. VLanId and PortMask must be set for that particular entry prior to setting this object. Switch software will base on that VLAN information to set the entire VLAN. Note: All the intended attributes of the given row of the table (given VLAN) must be set prior setting this object. When this object is set, Set-All-VLAN action will take place simultaneously. The previous setting will be overwritten by the new one.

snSwPortSetAll.name: snSwPortSetAll
snSwPortSetAll.description: The value of this object is the index number of the snSwPortInfoTable (snSwPortInfoPortIndex). snSwPortInfoMonitorMode, snSwPortInfoTagMode, snSwPortInfoChnMode, snSwPortInfoSpeed, snSwPortInfoAdminStatus are all the read-write attributes of that row of table. They will be used to set the same attributes for all the ports in the system. Note: prior setting this object, all the intended attributes of the given row of the table must be set. Otherwise, the current data of the row will be used to set the entire port-table. The previous setting will be overwritten by the new one.

snFdbTableCurEntry.name: snFdbTableCurEntry
snFdbTableCurEntry.description: The current total entry number of FDB are configured.

snFdbTableStationFlush.name: snFdbTableStationFlush
snFdbTableStationFlush.description: The following values of the flush state can only be read: normal(1)... normal state error(2)... operation failed flushing(4)... in process The following value can be written: flush(3).....do flush The agent will return a response even before the flush is done. And the read value will be flushing until flush is done. And the flush request will be rejected until error or normal.

snPortStpSetAll.name: snPortStpSetAll
snPortStpSetAll.description: The value of this object is 1 which means invoking Port STP Set-all command. The snPortStpPriority, snPortStpPathCost, the read-write STP related attributes of the first row of table will be used to set the same attributes for all the ports in the system. Note: prior setting this object, all the intended attributes of the given row of the table must be set. Otherwise, the current data of the row will be used to set the entire port-table. The previous setting will be overwritten by the new one.

snSwProbePortNum.name: snSwProbePortNum
snSwProbePortNum.description: A chassis switch probe port is operated as a traffic analyzer port and only one port can be assigned in the chassis. The bit 0 to bit 7: port number. The bit 8 to bit 11: slot number. A stackable switch is only assigned with one probe port as a traffic analyzer.

snSw8021qTagMode.name: snSw8021qTagMode
snSw8021qTagMode.description: The Switch Group is configured with the IEEE802.1q Tagging mode either enabled or disabled and the default is disabled mode. enabled(1)...........activate IEEE802.1q Tagging mode. disabled(0)..........no IEEE802.1q Tagging.

snSwGlobalStpMode.name: snSwGlobalStpMode
snSwGlobalStpMode.description: Spanning Tree System Global Mode in the Switch Group can be set either enabled or disabled and the default is enabled mode. enabled(1)...........activate Spanning Tree disabled(0)..........no Spanning Tree

snSwIpMcastQuerierMode.name: snSwIpMcastQuerierMode
snSwIpMcastQuerierMode.description: The IP Multicast pruning mode is configured either Non-Querier or Querier mode and the default is querier mode. querier(1)...........when prunning traffic locally within the VLAN. nonQuerier(2)........when running with a multicast capable router in the network.

snSwViolatorPortNumber.name: snSwViolatorPortNumber
snSwViolatorPortNumber.description: The port number of the switch or router that received a violator packet. It is included in the locked address violation trap. The bit 0 to bit 7: port number. The bit 8 to bit 11: slot number (slot for chassis only).

snSwViolatorMacAddress.name: snSwViolatorMacAddress
snSwViolatorMacAddress.description: The source address of the violator packet received by the switch or router. It is included in the locked address violation trap.

snVLanGroupVlanMaxEntry.name: snVLanGroupVlanMaxEntry
snVLanGroupVlanMaxEntry.description: The maximum number of VLAN entries are allowed to configure.

snSwEosBufferSize.name: snSwEosBufferSize
snSwEosBufferSize.description: A specific buffer size for all the different EOS buffers.

snVLanByPortEntrySize.name: snVLanByPortEntrySize
snVLanByPortEntrySize.description: The size of each VLAN table entry.

snSwPortEntrySize.name: snSwPortEntrySize
snSwPortEntrySize.description: The size of each port table entry.

snFdbStationEntrySize.name: snFdbStationEntrySize
snFdbStationEntrySize.description: The size of each Fdb station table entry.

snPortStpEntrySize.name: snPortStpEntrySize
snPortStpEntrySize.description: The size of each port stp table entry.

snSwEnableBridgeNewRootTrap.name: snSwEnableBridgeNewRootTrap
snSwEnableBridgeNewRootTrap.description: Indicates whether the SNMP agent process is permitted to generate bridge new root traps.

snSwEnableBridgeTopoChangeTrap.name: snSwEnableBridgeTopoChangeTrap
snSwEnableBridgeTopoChangeTrap.description: Indicates whether the SNMP agent process is permitted to generate bridge topology change traps.

snSwEnableLockedAddrViolationTrap.name: snSwEnableLockedAddrViolationTrap
snSwEnableLockedAddrViolationTrap.description: Indicates whether the SNMP agent process is permitted to generate locked address violation traps.

snSwIpxL3SwMode.name: snSwIpxL3SwMode
snSwIpxL3SwMode.description: The Switch Group is configured with the Layer3 IPX Switch mode either enabled or disabled and the default is disabled mode. enabled(1)...........activate Layer3 Switch disabled(0)..........disable Layer3 Switch

snVLanByIpSubnetMaxSubnets.name: snVLanByIpSubnetMaxSubnets
snVLanByIpSubnetMaxSubnets.description: The maximum number of subnets for each IP VLAN.

snVLanByIpxNetMaxNetworks.name: snVLanByIpxNetMaxNetworks
snVLanByIpxNetMaxNetworks.description: The maximum number of networks for each IPX VLAN.

snSwProtocolVLanMode.name: snSwProtocolVLanMode
snSwProtocolVLanMode.description: disabled(0) - represents system with Protocol VLAN disabled. enabled(1) - represents system with Protocol VLAN enabled (Layer3 VLAN).

snMacStationVLanId.name: snMacStationVLanId
snMacStationVLanId.description: This MAC Station VLAN ID index to the standard Forwarding Database for Transparent Bridge Table. (dot1dTpFdbTable). Since the dot1dTpFdbTable index is the MAC Address assigned to one of the ports in the bridge(VLAN) and each MAC address can be re-assigned to a different ports belonging to different bridges(VLANs), the snMacStationVLanId can be used by users to specify which bridge(VLAN) MAC Station information of the dot1dTpFdbTable users want to retrieve. If users do not specify the VLan ID in this MIB, the default VLAN (bridge) ID will be used when dot1dTpFdbTable is retrieved.

snSwClearCounters.name: snSwClearCounters
snSwClearCounters.description: valid(0) - a SNMP-GET of this mib shows that it is valid command to use. clear(1) - represents clear counter command of the following counters: Dot3, MIB2, IP and IPX counters for all ports.

snSw8021qTagType.name: snSw8021qTagType
snSw8021qTagType.description: The IEEE802.1q tag type embedded in the length/type field of an Ethernet packet. It specifies that the 2 octets after the length/type field in an Ethernet packet is the tag value.

snSwBroadcastLimit.name: snSwBroadcastLimit
snSwBroadcastLimit.description: Limit the number of broadcast packets to forward out of the switch ports. This object specifies the number of broadcast packets per second. Setting a value of 0 to this object disables the limitation check.

snSwMaxMacFilterPerSystem.name: snSwMaxMacFilterPerSystem
snSwMaxMacFilterPerSystem.description: The maximum number of MAC Filters per system in the MAC Filter table.

snSwMaxMacFilterPerPort.name: snSwMaxMacFilterPerPort
snSwMaxMacFilterPerPort.description: The maximum number of MAC Filters per port in the Port MAC Access Filter table.

snSwDefaultVLanId.name: snSwDefaultVLanId
snSwDefaultVLanId.description: The VLAN ID of the DEFAULT PORT-VLAN.

snSwGlobalAutoNegotiate.name: snSwGlobalAutoNegotiate
snSwGlobalAutoNegotiate.description: This feature only applies to Gigabit Ethernet ports. If set to disable(0), all Gigabit Ethernet ports will be put to non- negotiation mode. If set to enable(1), all Gigabit Ethernet ports will start auto-negotiation indefinitely until succeed. If set to negFullAuto(2), all Gigabit Ethernet ports will start with auto-negotiation, if the negotiation failed, then they will automatically switch to non-negotiation mode. Stackable products (except TurboIron 8) Gigabit Ethernet ports do not support negFullAuto(2). If the snSwPortInfoAutoNegotiate value of a port was not set to global, this global value does not apply to the negotiation mode of that port.

snSwQosMechanism.name: snSwQosMechanism
snSwQosMechanism.description: Indicates whether the qos mechanism is strict or weighted.

snSwSingleStpMode.name: snSwSingleStpMode
snSwSingleStpMode.description: Single Spanning Tree System Mode in the Switch Group can be set either enabled or disabled and the default is disabled mode. enabled(1)...........activate Single Spanning Tree disabled(0)..........no Single Spanning Tree

snSwFastStpMode.name: snSwFastStpMode
snSwFastStpMode.description: Fast Spanning Tree System Mode in the Switch Group can be set either enabled or disabled and the default is enabled mode. enabled(1)...........activate Fast Spanning Tree disabled(0)..........no Fast Spanning Tree

snVLanByPortTable.name: snVLanByPortTable
snVLanByPortTable.description: If snSwGroupOperMode is configured as basic mode which is VLAN by Port, Layer2 switching, then this table is valid. Each VLAN switch port could have a number of VLAN IDs.

snVLanByPortEntry.name: snVLanByPortEntry
snVLanByPortEntry.description: An entry in the VLAN By Port Information table. snVLanByPortVLanIndex = 1 and with snVLanByPortVLanId = 1 together implies all attributes applying to the Global switch group i.e. noVLan. A SNMP SET PDU for a row of the snVLanByPortTable requires the entired sequence of the MIB Objects in each snVLanByPortEntry stored in one PDU. Otherwise, GENERR return-value will be returned.

snVLanByPortVLanIndex.name: snVLanByPortVLanIndex
snVLanByPortVLanIndex.description: The VLAN ID index must not be greater than the snVLanGroupVlanMaxEntry. Each VLAN Identifier can have a membership of multiple ports.

snVLanByPortVLanId.name: snVLanByPortVLanId
snVLanByPortVLanId.description: The VLAN ID index to the VLAN By Port Info Table. Each VLAN Identifier can have a membership of multiple ports.

snVLanByPortPortMask.name: snVLanByPortPortMask
snVLanByPortPortMask.description: The Standand-alone switch VLAN port membership. (It was obsoleted for Chassis Product)

snVLanByPortQos.name: snVLanByPortQos
snVLanByPortQos.description: The Stand alone stackable switch VLAN Priority values are: low(0) -- low prority high(1) -- high prority. The BigIron switch VLAN Priority values are: level0(0), level1(1), level2(2), level3(3), level4(4), level5(5), level6(6), level7(7)

snVLanByPortStpMode.name: snVLanByPortStpMode
snVLanByPortStpMode.description: Spanning Tree Mode in the Switch Group can be set either enabled or disabled and the default is enabled mode. enabled(1)...........activate Spanning Tree disabled(0)..........no Spanning Tree

snVLanByPortStpPriority.name: snVLanByPortStpPriority
snVLanByPortStpPriority.description: dot1dStpPriority : The value of the write-able portion of the Stp ID, i.e., the first two octets of the (8 octet long) Bridge ID. The other (last) 6 octets of the Bridge ID are given by the value of the base bridge address - dot1dBaseBridgeAddress.

snVLanByPortStpGroupMaxAge.name: snVLanByPortStpGroupMaxAge
snVLanByPortStpGroupMaxAge.description: dot1dStpBridgeMaxAge: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The value that all bridges use for MaxAge when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that 802.1D-1990 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of dot1dStpBridgeHelloTime. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

snVLanByPortStpGroupHelloTime.name: snVLanByPortStpGroupHelloTime
snVLanByPortStpGroupHelloTime.description: dot1dStpBridgeHelloTime: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The value that all bridges use for HelloTime when this bridge is acting as the root. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D- 1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

snVLanByPortStpGroupForwardDelay.name: snVLanByPortStpGroupForwardDelay
snVLanByPortStpGroupForwardDelay.description: dot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay : From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The value that all bridges use for ForwardDelay when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that 802.1D-1990 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of dot1dStpBridgeMaxAge. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

snVLanByPortRowStatus.name: snVLanByPortRowStatus
snVLanByPortRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row modify(5)...modifies an exsisting row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. Deleted rows go away immediately. The following values can be returned on reads: noSuch(0)...no such row other(1)....some other case valid(2)....the row exists and is valid

snVLanByPortOperState.name: snVLanByPortOperState
snVLanByPortOperState.description: By default, this mode is set to notActivated(0). notActivated(0)...the VLAN entry is not activated and not in running mode. activated(1)......the VLAN entry is activated and in running mode

snVLanByPortBaseNumPorts.name: snVLanByPortBaseNumPorts
snVLanByPortBaseNumPorts.description: The number of ports controlled by this bridging entity.

snVLanByPortBaseType.name: snVLanByPortBaseType
snVLanByPortBaseType.description: Indicates what type of bridging this bridge can perform. If a bridge is actually performing a certain type of bridging this will be indicated by entries in the port table for the given type.

snVLanByPortStpProtocolSpecification.name: snVLanByPortStpProtocolSpecification
snVLanByPortStpProtocolSpecification.description: An indication of what version of the Spanning Tree Protocol is being run. The value 'decLb100(2)' indicates the DEC LANbridge 100 Spanning Tree protocol. IEEE 802.1d implementations will return 'ieee8021d(3)'. If future versions of the IEEE Spanning Tree Protocol are released that are incompatible with the current version a new value will be defined.

snVLanByPortStpMaxAge.name: snVLanByPortStpMaxAge
snVLanByPortStpMaxAge.description: dot1dStpMaxAge: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The maximum age of Spanning Tree Protocol information learned from the network on any port before it is discarded, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

snVLanByPortStpHelloTime.name: snVLanByPortStpHelloTime
snVLanByPortStpHelloTime.description: dot1dStpHelloTime: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The amount of time between the transmission of Configuration bridge PDUs by this node on any port when it is the root of the spanning tree or trying to become so, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

snVLanByPortStpHoldTime.name: snVLanByPortStpHoldTime
snVLanByPortStpHoldTime.description: dot1dStpHoldTime: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). This time value determines the interval length during which no more than two Configuration bridge PDUs shall be transmitted by this node, in units of hundredths of a second.

snVLanByPortStpForwardDelay.name: snVLanByPortStpForwardDelay
snVLanByPortStpForwardDelay.description: dot1dStpForwardDelay: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). This time value, measured in units of hundredths of a second, controls how fast a port changes its spanning state when moving towards the Forwarding state. The value determines how long the port stays in each of the Listening and Learning states, which precede the Forwarding state. This value is also used, when a topology change has been detected and is underway, to age all dynamic entries in the Forwarding Database. [Note that this value is the one that this bridge is currently using, in contrast to dot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay which is the value that this bridge and all others would start using if/when this bridge were to become the root.]

snVLanByPortStpTimeSinceTopologyChange.name: snVLanByPortStpTimeSinceTopologyChange
snVLanByPortStpTimeSinceTopologyChange.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the last time a topology change was detected by the bridge entity.

snVLanByPortStpTopChanges.name: snVLanByPortStpTopChanges
snVLanByPortStpTopChanges.description: The total number of topology changes detected by this bridge since the management entity was last reset or initialized.

snVLanByPortStpRootCost.name: snVLanByPortStpRootCost
snVLanByPortStpRootCost.description: dot1dStpRootCost: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The cost of the path to the root as seen from this bridge.

snVLanByPortStpRootPort.name: snVLanByPortStpRootPort
snVLanByPortStpRootPort.description: dot1dStpRootPort: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The port number of the port which offers the lowest cost path from this bridge to the root bridge.

snVLanByPortStpDesignatedRoot.name: snVLanByPortStpDesignatedRoot
snVLanByPortStpDesignatedRoot.description: dot1dStpDesignatedRoot: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The bridge identifier of the root of the spanning tree as determined by the Spanning Tree Protocol as executed by this node. This value is used as the Root Identifier parameter in all Configuration Bridge PDUs originated by this node.

snVLanByPortBaseBridgeAddress.name: snVLanByPortBaseBridgeAddress
snVLanByPortBaseBridgeAddress.description: The MAC address used by this bridge when it must be referred to in a unique fashion. It is recommended that this be the numerically smallest MAC address of all ports that belong to this bridge. However it is only required to be unique. When concatenated with dot1dStpPriority a unique BridgeIdentifier is formed which is used in the Spanning Tree Protocol.

snVLanByPortRouterIntf.name: snVLanByPortRouterIntf
snVLanByPortRouterIntf.description: Optional: A virtual interface for router to the VLAN -- applied to router only. If a SNMP-Get value is zero, that means this object was not configured.

snVLanByPortChassisPortMask.name: snVLanByPortChassisPortMask
snVLanByPortChassisPortMask.description: The Chassis VLAN switch port membership. (It was obsoleted after release 07100, replaced by snVLanByPortPortList)

snVLanByPortPortList.name: snVLanByPortPortList
snVLanByPortPortList.description: A list of port indices which are the port membership of a VLAN By Port. Each port index is a 16-bit integer in big endian order. 8-bit is the slot number, the other 8-bit is the port number.

snVLanByPortMemberTable.name: snVLanByPortMemberTable
snVLanByPortMemberTable.description: Port VLAN (Layer 2 VLAN) port membership table.

snVLanByPortMemberEntry.name: snVLanByPortMemberEntry
snVLanByPortMemberEntry.description: An entry of the port VLAN membership table.

snVLanByPortMemberPortId.name: snVLanByPortMemberPortId
snVLanByPortMemberPortId.description: The ifIndex which is a member of the port VLAN.

snVLanByPortMemberRowStatus.name: snVLanByPortMemberRowStatus
snVLanByPortMemberRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. Deleted rows go away immediately. The following values can be returned on reads: noSuch(0)...no such row other(1)....some other case valid(2)....the row exists and is valid

snVLanByPortCfgEntry.name: snVLanByPortCfgEntry
snVLanByPortCfgEntry.description: An entry of the port VLAN configuration table.

snVLanByPortCfgQos.name: snVLanByPortCfgQos
snVLanByPortCfgQos.description: The Stand alone stackable switch VLAN Priority values are: level0(0) -- low prority level1(1) -- high prority. The BigIron switch VLAN Priority values are: level0(0), level1(1), level2(2), level3(3), level4(4), level5(5), level6(6), level7(7)

snVLanByPortCfgStpMode.name: snVLanByPortCfgStpMode
snVLanByPortCfgStpMode.description: Spanning Tree Mode in the Switch Group can be set either enabled or disabled and the default is enabled mode. enabled(1)...........activate Spanning Tree disabled(0)..........no Spanning Tree

snVLanByPortCfgStpPriority.name: snVLanByPortCfgStpPriority
snVLanByPortCfgStpPriority.description: dot1dStpPriority : The value of the write-able portion of the Stp ID, i.e., the first two octets of the (8 octet long) Bridge ID. The other (last) 6 octets of the Bridge ID are given by the value of the base bridge address - dot1dBaseBridgeAddress.

snVLanByPortCfgStpGroupMaxAge.name: snVLanByPortCfgStpGroupMaxAge
snVLanByPortCfgStpGroupMaxAge.description: dot1dStpBridgeMaxAge: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The value that all bridges use for MaxAge when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that 802.1D-1990 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of dot1dStpBridgeHelloTime. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

snVLanByPortCfgStpGroupHelloTime.description: dot1dStpBridgeHelloTime: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The value that all bridges use for HelloTime when this bridge is acting as the root. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D- 1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

snVLanByPortCfgStpGroupForwardDelay.name: snVLanByPortCfgStpGroupForwardDelay
snVLanByPortCfgStpGroupForwardDelay.description: dot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay : From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The value that all bridges use for ForwardDelay when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that 802.1D-1990 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of dot1dStpBridgeMaxAge. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

snVLanByPortCfgBaseNumPorts.name: snVLanByPortCfgBaseNumPorts
snVLanByPortCfgBaseNumPorts.description: The number of ports controlled by this bridging entity.

snVLanByPortCfgBaseType.name: snVLanByPortCfgBaseType
snVLanByPortCfgBaseType.description: Indicates what type of bridging this bridge can perform. If a bridge is actually performing a certain type of bridging this will be indicated by entries in the port table for the given type.

snVLanByPortCfgStpProtocolSpecification.name: snVLanByPortCfgStpProtocolSpecification
snVLanByPortCfgStpProtocolSpecification.description: An indication of what version of the Spanning Tree Protocol is being run. The value 'decLb100(2)' indicates the DEC LANbridge 100 Spanning Tree protocol. IEEE 802.1d implementations will return 'ieee8021d(3)'. If future versions of the IEEE Spanning Tree Protocol are released that are incompatible with the current version a new value will be defined.

snVLanByPortCfgStpMaxAge.name: snVLanByPortCfgStpMaxAge
snVLanByPortCfgStpMaxAge.description: dot1dStpMaxAge: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The maximum age of Spanning Tree Protocol information learned from the network on any port before it is discarded, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

snVLanByPortCfgStpHelloTime.name: snVLanByPortCfgStpHelloTime
snVLanByPortCfgStpHelloTime.description: dot1dStpHelloTime: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The amount of time between the transmission of Configuration bridge PDUs by this node on any port when it is the root of the spanning tree or trying to become so, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

snVLanByPortCfgStpHoldTime.description: dot1dStpHoldTime: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). This time value determines the interval length during which no more than two Configuration bridge PDUs shall be transmitted by this node, in units of hundredths of a second.

snVLanByPortCfgStpForwardDelay.name: snVLanByPortCfgStpForwardDelay
snVLanByPortCfgStpForwardDelay.description: dot1dStpForwardDelay: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). This time value, measured in units of hundredths of a second, controls how fast a port changes its spanning state when moving towards the Forwarding state. The value determines how long the port stays in each of the Listening and Learning states, which precede the Forwarding state. snVLanByPortCfgStpTimeSinceTopologyChang.name: snVLanByPortCfgStpTimeSinceTopologyChange
snVLanByPortCfgStpTimeSinceTopologyChang.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the last time a topology change was detected by the bridge entity.

snVLanByPortCfgStpTopChanges.name: snVLanByPortCfgStpTopChanges
snVLanByPortCfgStpTopChanges.description: The total number of topology changes detected by this bridge since the management entity was last reset or initialized.

snVLanByPortCfgStpRootCost.name: snVLanByPortCfgStpRootCost
snVLanByPortCfgStpRootCost.description: dot1dStpRootCost: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The cost of the path to the root as seen from this bridge.

snVLanByPortCfgStpRootPort.name: snVLanByPortCfgStpRootPort
snVLanByPortCfgStpRootPort.description: dot1dStpRootPort: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The port number of the port which offers the lowest cost path from this bridge to the root bridge.

snVLanByPortCfgStpDesignatedRoot.name: snVLanByPortCfgStpDesignatedRoot
snVLanByPortCfgStpDesignatedRoot.description: dot1dStpDesignatedRoot: From RFC1493(Bridge MIB). The bridge identifier of the root of the spanning tree as determined by the Spanning Tree Protocol as executed by this node. This value is used as the Root Identifier parameter in all Configuration Bridge PDUs originated by this node.

snVLanByPortCfgBaseBridgeAddress.name: snVLanByPortCfgBaseBridgeAddress
snVLanByPortCfgBaseBridgeAddress.description: The MAC address used by this bridge when it must be referred to in a unique fashion. snSwPortInfoTable.name: snSwPortInfoTable
snSwPortInfoTable.description: A specific snSwPortInfo group consists of a number of switch ports.

snSwPortInfoEntry.name: snSwPortInfoEntry
snSwPortInfoEntry.description: An entry in the snSwPortInfo table indicates the configuration on a specified port. A SNMP SET PDU for a row of the snSwPortInfoTable requires the entired sequence of the MIB Objects in each snSwPortInfoEntry stored in one PDU. Otherwise, GENERR return-value will be returned.

snSwPortInfoPortNum.name: snSwPortInfoPortNum
snSwPortInfoPortNum.description: The port index. The bit 0 to bit 7: port number. The bit 8 to bit 11: slot number (slot for chassis only).

snSwPortInfoMonitorMode.name: snSwPortInfoMonitorMode
snSwPortInfoMonitorMode.description: A monitoring port is selected and its traffic will be analyzed if the mode is not disabled(0), which is the default mode. The values are: disabled(0) -- No traffic monitoring input(1) -- traffic monitoring is activated on packets received output(2) -- traffic monitoring is activated on packets transmitted both(3) -- traffic monitoring is activated on packets received and transmitted.

snSwPortInfoTagMode.name: snSwPortInfoTagMode
snSwPortInfoTagMode.description: For tagged port, we could have multiple VLANs per port. For untagged port or auto port, there is only one VLAN ID per port.

snSwPortInfoChnMode.name: snSwPortInfoChnMode
snSwPortInfoChnMode.description: The port can be configured to operate in either half or full duplex mode. The values are: halfDuplex(1)...half duplex mode fullDuplex(2)...full duplex mode The read-back channel status from hardware are: none(0).........link down or port disabled. halfDuplex(1)...half duplex mode fullDuplex(2)...full duplex mode The port media type (expansion or regular) and port link type (trunk or feeder) determine value of this object. The port can not set to half duplex mode if the port connect mode is m200e(4). However, the value of this parameter may be automatically set whenever the expansion port is connected (e.g. cascade connecting device).

snSwPortInfoSpeed.name: snSwPortInfoSpeed
snSwPortInfoSpeed.description: The speed configuration for a port. The values are: none(0)..........link down or no traffic. sAutoSense(1)....Auto-sensing 10 or 100Mbits. s10M(2)..........10Mbits per second. s100M(3).........100Mbits per second. s1G(4)...........1Gbits per second. s45M(5)..........45Mbits per second (T3) (for expansion board only). s155M(6).........155Mbits per second (ATM) (for expansion board only). s10G(7)..........10Gbits per second. The read-back hardware status are the following: none(0)..........link down or no traffic. s10M(2)..........10Mbits per second. s100M(3).........100Mbits per second. s1G(4)...........1Gbits per second. s45M(5)..........45Mbits per second (T3) (for expansion board only). s155M(6).........155Mbits per second (ATM) (for expansion board only). s10G(7)..........10Gbits per second. The port media type (expansion or regular) and port link type (trunk or feeder) determine whether this object can be written and the valid values. It is not allowed to change speed for trunks ports. For expansion ports, all of the above speed can be set. However, the value of this parameter may be automatically set whenever the expansion port is connected (e.g. cascade connecting device).

snSwPortInfoMediaType.name: snSwPortInfoMediaType
snSwPortInfoMediaType.description: The media type for the port. The values are: other(1).........other or unknown media. m100BaseTX(2)....100Mbits per second copper. m100BaseFX(3)....100Mbits per second fiber. m1000BaseFX(4)...1Gbits per second fiber. mT3(5)...........45Mbits per second (T3). m155ATM(6).......155Mbits per second (ATM). m1000BaseTX(7)...1Gbits per second copper. m622ATM(8).......622Mbits per second (ATM). m155POS(9).......155Mbits per second (POS). m622POS(10)......622Mbits per second (POS). m2488POS(11).....2488Mbits per second (POS). m10000BaseFX(12).10Gbits per second fiber.

snSwPortInfoConnectorType.name: snSwPortInfoConnectorType
snSwPortInfoConnectorType.description: The type of connector that the port offers. The values are: other(1)...........other or unknown connector copper(2)..........Copper connector fiber(3)...........Fiber connector This describes the physical connector type

snSwPortInfoAdminStatus.name: snSwPortInfoAdminStatus
snSwPortInfoAdminStatus.description: The desired state of all ports. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed. (same as ifAdminStatus in MIB-II)

snSwPortInfoLinkStatus.name: snSwPortInfoLinkStatus
snSwPortInfoLinkStatus.description: The current operational state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed. (same as ifOperStatus in MIB-II)

snSwPortInfoPortQos.name: snSwPortInfoPortQos
snSwPortInfoPortQos.description: The Stand alone stackable switch Port Qos Priority values are: low(0) -- low prority high(1) -- high prority. The BigIron Port Qos Priority values are: level0(0), level1(1), level2(2), level3(3), level4(4), level5(5), level6(6), level7(7)

snSwPortInfoPhysAddress.name: snSwPortInfoPhysAddress
snSwPortInfoPhysAddress.description: The port physical address. The physical address represents the switch port.

snSwPortStatsInFrames.name: snSwPortStatsInFrames
snSwPortStatsInFrames.description: The total number of packets received on the interface.

snSwPortStatsOutFrames.name: snSwPortStatsOutFrames
snSwPortStatsOutFrames.description: The total number of packets transmitted out of the interface.

snSwPortStatsAlignErrors.name: snSwPortStatsAlignErrors
snSwPortStatsAlignErrors.description: dot3StatsAlignmentErrors : A count of frames received on a particular interface that are not an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the alignmentError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

snSwPortStatsFCSErrors.name: snSwPortStatsFCSErrors
snSwPortStatsFCSErrors.description: dot3StatsFCSErrors : A count of frames received on a particular interface that are an integral number of octets in length but do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameCheckError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

snSwPortStatsMultiColliFrames.name: snSwPortStatsMultiColliFrames
snSwPortStatsMultiColliFrames.description: dot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames : A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts, ifOutMulticastPkts, or ifOutBroadcastPkts, and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the dot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames object.

snSwPortStatsFrameTooLongs.name: snSwPortStatsFrameTooLongs
snSwPortStatsFrameTooLongs.description: dot3StatsFrameTooLongs : A count of frames received on a particular interface that exceed the maximum permitted frame size. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameTooLong status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

snSwPortStatsTxColliFrames.name: snSwPortStatsTxColliFrames
snSwPortStatsTxColliFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. A frame that is counted by a combination of both dot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames and dot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames objects.

snSwPortStatsRxColliFrames.name: snSwPortStatsRxColliFrames
snSwPortStatsRxColliFrames.description: A count of successfully received frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. This object is not specified in dot3 but it has the same functionarity as snSwPortStatsTxColliFrames.

snSwPortStatsFrameTooShorts.name: snSwPortStatsFrameTooShorts
snSwPortStatsFrameTooShorts.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that below the minimum permitted frame size.

snSwPortLockAddressCount.name: snSwPortLockAddressCount
snSwPortLockAddressCount.description: The number of source MAC addresses are allowed for a port. Writing 0 to this object will allow any number of addresses.

snSwPortStpPortEnable.name: snSwPortStpPortEnable
snSwPortStpPortEnable.description: The enabled/disabled status of the port.

snSwPortDhcpGateListId.name: snSwPortDhcpGateListId
snSwPortDhcpGateListId.description: The ID for a DHCP gateway list entry relative to this switch port. 0 = unset or no assigned ID

snSwPortStatsInBcastFrames.name: snSwPortStatsInBcastFrames
snSwPortStatsInBcastFrames.description: The total number of broadcast packets received on the interface.

snSwPortStatsOutBcastFrames.name: snSwPortStatsOutBcastFrames
snSwPortStatsOutBcastFrames.description: The total number of broadcast packets transmitted out of the interface.

snSwPortStatsInMcastFrames.name: snSwPortStatsInMcastFrames
snSwPortStatsInMcastFrames.description: The total number of multicast packets received on the interface.

snSwPortStatsOutMcastFrames.name: snSwPortStatsOutMcastFrames
snSwPortStatsOutMcastFrames.description: The total number of multicast packets transmitted out of the interface.

snSwPortStatsInDiscard.name: snSwPortStatsInDiscard
snSwPortStatsInDiscard.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

snSwPortStatsOutDiscard.name: snSwPortStatsOutDiscard
snSwPortStatsOutDiscard.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

snSwPortStatsMacStations.name: snSwPortStatsMacStations
snSwPortStatsMacStations.description: The total number of MAC Stations connected to the interface.

snSwPortCacheGroupId.name: snSwPortCacheGroupId
snSwPortCacheGroupId.description: Cache Group ID for the interface.

snSwPortTransGroupId.name: snSwPortTransGroupId
snSwPortTransGroupId.description: Transparent Group ID for the interface.

snSwPortInfoAutoNegotiate.name: snSwPortInfoAutoNegotiate
snSwPortInfoAutoNegotiate.description: This feature only applies to Gigabit Ethernet ports. If set to disable(0), port will be put to non-negotiation mode. If set to enable(1), port will start auto-negotiation indefinitely until succeed. If set to negFullAuto(2), the port will start with auto- negotiation, if the negotiation failed, then it will automatically switch to non-negotiation mode. Stackable products (except TurboIron 8) Gigabit Ethernet ports do not support negFullAuto(2). If set to global(3), port negotiation mode follows the value of snSwGlobalAutoNegotiate. Non-Gigabit Ethernet port returns the value other(4).

snSwPortInfoGigType.name: snSwPortInfoGigType
snSwPortInfoGigType.description: The media type for the port. The values are: m1000BaseSX(0)....1Gbits per second fiber, with a short wavelength transceiver. m1000BaseLX(1)....1Gbits per second fiber, with a long wavelength transceiver (3km). m1000BaseLH(2)....1Gbits per second fiber, with a special wavelength transceiver (50km). m1000BaseLHA(3)....1Gbits per second fiber, with a special wavelength transceiver (70km). m1000BaseLHB(4)....1Gbits per second fiber, with a special wavelength transceiver (150km). m1000BaseTX(5)....1Gbits per second copper (100meter). m10000BaseSR(6)....10Gbits per second fiber, with a short range wavelength transceiver (100m). m10000BaseLR(7)....10Gbits per second fiber, with a long range wavelength transceiver (10km). m10000BaseER(8)....10Gbits per second fiber, with a extended range wavelength transceiver (40km). notApplicable(255)....a non-gigabit port.

snSwPortStatsLinkChange.name: snSwPortStatsLinkChange
snSwPortStatsLinkChange.description: The total number of link state change of the interface.

snSwPortIfIndex.name: snSwPortIfIndex
snSwPortIfIndex.description: In order to identify a particular interface, this object shall identify the instance of the ifIndex object, defined in RFC 1213 and RFC 1573.

snSwPortDescr.name: snSwPortDescr
snSwPortDescr.description: A textual string containing the slot/port information about the interface.

snSwPortInOctets.name: snSwPortInOctets
snSwPortInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters. This object is a 64-bit counter of the ifInOctets object, defined in RFC 1213. The octet string is in big-endian byte order.

snSwPortOutOctets.name: snSwPortOutOctets
snSwPortOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters. This object is a 64-bit counter of the ifOutOctets object, defined in RFC 1213. The octet string is in big-endian byte order.

snSwPortStatsInBitsPerSec.name: snSwPortStatsInBitsPerSec
snSwPortStatsInBitsPerSec.description: The number of bits per second received on the interface over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwPortStatsOutBitsPerSec.name: snSwPortStatsOutBitsPerSec
snSwPortStatsOutBitsPerSec.description: The number of bits per second transmitted out of the interface over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwPortStatsInPktsPerSec.name: snSwPortStatsInPktsPerSec
snSwPortStatsInPktsPerSec.description: The number of packets per second received on the interface over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwPortStatsOutPktsPerSec.name: snSwPortStatsOutPktsPerSec
snSwPortStatsOutPktsPerSec.description: The number of packets per second transmitted out of the interface over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwPortStatsInUtilization.name: snSwPortStatsInUtilization
snSwPortStatsInUtilization.description: The input network utilization in hundredths of a percent over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwPortStatsOutUtilization.name: snSwPortStatsOutUtilization
snSwPortStatsOutUtilization.description: The output network utilization in hundredths of a percent over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwPortFastSpanPortEnable.name: snSwPortFastSpanPortEnable
snSwPortFastSpanPortEnable.description: The enabled/disabled fast span port status of the port.

snSwPortFastSpanUplinkEnable.name: snSwPortFastSpanUplinkEnable
snSwPortFastSpanUplinkEnable.description: The enabled/disabled fast span uplink status of the port.

snSwPortVlanId.name: snSwPortVlanId
snSwPortVlanId.description: The ID of a VLAN of which this port is a member. Port must be untagged. For tagged port which belongs to multiple VLANs, this object return 0 which is an invalid VLAN ID value.

snSwPortRouteOnly.name: snSwPortRouteOnly
snSwPortRouteOnly.description: Enable/Disable L2 switching of a routing switch port. By default, the routing switch performs routing first. If routing failed, it performs switching. Enable route only instrcuts the routing switch to perform routing only. For a L2 switching only product, reading this object always return 'disabled', writing 'enabled' to this object takes no effect.

snSwPortPresent.name: snSwPortPresent
snSwPortPresent.description: Indicate if the port is absent or present. This object only valid for M4 module

snSwPortGBICStatus.name: snSwPortGBICStatus
snSwPortGBICStatus.description: Indicate if the gig port has GBICs on them. If set to GBIC(1), it means that the port is GBIC. If set to miniGBIC(2), it means that the port miniGBIC. If set to empty(3), it means that the GBIC is missing. Value other(4) means that the port not a removable gig port.

snSwPortStatsInKiloBitsPerSec.name: snSwPortStatsInKiloBitsPerSec
snSwPortStatsInKiloBitsPerSec.description: Bit rate in kilobits per second received on the 10G and faster interface over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwPortStatsOutKiloBitsPerSec.name: snSwPortStatsOutKiloBitsPerSec
snSwPortStatsOutKiloBitsPerSec.description: Bit rate in kilobits per second transmitted out of the 10G and faster interface over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwPortLoadInterval.name: snSwPortLoadInterval
snSwPortLoadInterval.description: The time in seconds for which average port utilization should be carried out. The value should be incremental of 30 seconds, between the ranges specified.

snSwPortTagType.name: snSwPortTagType
snSwPortTagType.description: The IEEE802.1q tag type embedded in the length/type field of an Ethernet packet. It specifies that the 2 octets after the length/type field in an Ethernet packet is the tag value.

snFdbTable.name: snFdbTable
snFdbTable.description: This table contains snFdb information for each station known to the system, one entry per station.

snFdbEntry.name: snFdbEntry
snFdbEntry.description: Each entry represents the information of a static MAC station.

snFdbStationIndex.name: snFdbStationIndex
snFdbStationIndex.description: The FDB Station index to the Fdb Station Table.

snFdbStationAddr.name: snFdbStationAddr
snFdbStationAddr.description: The snFdbs physical address. The physical address represents a MAC Station.

snFdbStationPort.name: snFdbStationPort
snFdbStationPort.description: Station slot/port number. The bit 0 to bit 7: port number. The bit 8 to bit 11: slot number (slot for chassis only).

snFdbStationQos.name: snFdbStationQos
snFdbStationQos.description: The Stand alone stackable station Qos Priority values are: low(0) -- low prority high(1) -- high prority. The BigIron switch station Priority values are: level0(0), level1(1), level2(2), level3(3), level4(4), level5(5), level6(6), level7(7)

snFdbStationType.name: snFdbStationType
snFdbStationType.description: The station type values are: notSupported -- a read value only : this product does not support MultiLayer Switching. host -- any MAC station. router -- a router-typed station.

snFdbRowStatus.name: snFdbRowStatus
snFdbRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. Deleted rows go away immediately. The following values can be returned on reads: noSuch(0)...no such row other(1)....some other case valid(2)....the row exists and is valid

snPortStpTable.name: snPortStpTable
snPortStpTable.description: A specific snPortStpTable consists of a number of switch ports. This table only exists if only if snVLanByPortTable exists and snVLanByPortStpMode is enabled for each VLAN.

snPortStpEntry.name: snPortStpEntry
snPortStpEntry.description: An entry in the snPortStpTable indicates the configuration on a specified port. A SNMP SET PDU for a row of the snPortStpTable requires the entired sequence of the MIB Objects in each snPortStpEntry stored in one PDU. Otherwise, GENERR return-value will be returned.

snPortStpVLanId.name: snPortStpVLanId
snPortStpVLanId.description: The VLAN ID of the VLAN switch community.

snPortStpPortNum.name: snPortStpPortNum
snPortStpPortNum.description: The port number of the Switch. The bit 0 to bit 7: port number. The bit 8 to bit 11: slot number (slot for chassis only).

snPortStpPortPriority.name: snPortStpPortPriority
snPortStpPortPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the first (in network byte order) octet of the (2 octet long) Port ID. The other octet of the Port ID is given by the value of dot1dStpPort.

snPortStpPathCost.name: snPortStpPathCost
snPortStpPathCost.description: dot1dStpPortPathCost : The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port. 802.1D-1990 recommends that the default value of this parameter be in inverse proportion to the speed of the attached LAN. Writing value zero to this object sets path cost to a default value which automatically changes according to port speed. Reading value zero indicates an unknown path cost value because port speed cannot be determined due to speed auto sense in progress.

snPortStpOperState.name: snPortStpOperState
snPortStpOperState.description: By default, this mode is set to notActivated(0). notActivated(0)...the Port STP entry is not activated and not in running mode. activated(1)......the Port STP entry is activated and in running mode

snPortStpPortEnable.name: snPortStpPortEnable
snPortStpPortEnable.description: The enabled/disabled status of the port.

snPortStpPortForwardTransitions.name: snPortStpPortForwardTransitions
snPortStpPortForwardTransitions.description: The number of times this port has transitioned from the Learning state to the Forwarding state.

snPortStpPortState.name: snPortStpPortState
snPortStpPortState.description: The port's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. This state controls what action a port takes on reception of a frame. If the bridge has detected a port that is malfunctioning it will place that port into the broken(6) state. For ports which are disabled (see dot1dStpPortEnable), this object will have a value of disabled(1).

snPortStpPortDesignatedCost.name: snPortStpPortDesignatedCost
snPortStpPortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the Designated Port of the segment connected to this port. This value is compared to the Root Path Cost field in received bridge PDUs.

snPortStpPortDesignatedRoot.name: snPortStpPortDesignatedRoot
snPortStpPortDesignatedRoot.description: The unique Bridge Identifier of the Bridge recorded as the Root in the Configuration BPDUs transmitted by the Designated Bridge for the segment to which the port is attached.

snPortStpPortDesignatedBridge.name: snPortStpPortDesignatedBridge
snPortStpPortDesignatedBridge.description: The Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

snPortStpPortDesignatedPort.name: snPortStpPortDesignatedPort
snPortStpPortDesignatedPort.description: The Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

snTrunkTable.name: snTrunkTable
snTrunkTable.description: A specific snTrunkTable consists of a number of Trunk port-mask.

snTrunkEntry.name: snTrunkEntry
snTrunkEntry.description: An entry in the snTrunkTable indicates the configuration on a specified Trunk port membership.

snTrunkIndex.name: snTrunkIndex
snTrunkIndex.description: The number of the trunk entries can be configured.

snTrunkType.name: snTrunkType
snTrunkType.description: The trunk connection type which specifies what device the trunk ports are connected to.

snMSTrunkTable.name: snMSTrunkTable
snMSTrunkTable.description: A table contains the configuration of port members of multi-slot trunk groups.

snMSTrunkPortIndex.name: snMSTrunkPortIndex
snMSTrunkPortIndex.description: The primary port of a trunk group. For module with Gig ports, primary port is port 1, 3, 5, 7. For module with 10/100 ports, primary port is port 1, 5, 9, 13, 17, 21.

snMSTrunkPortList.name: snMSTrunkPortList
snMSTrunkPortList.description: A list of port indices which are the port membership of a trunk group. Each port index is a 16-bit integer in big endian order. The first port index must be the primary port index.

snMSTrunkType.name: snMSTrunkType
snMSTrunkType.description: The trunk connection type which specifies what device the trunk ports are connected to.

snMSTrunkRowStatus.name: snMSTrunkRowStatus
snMSTrunkRowStatus.description: To create or delete a table entry.

snSwSummaryMode.name: snSwSummaryMode
snSwSummaryMode.description: The Switch Group Configuration Summary is configured either enabled or disabled and the default is disabled mode. enabled(1)...........activate Switch Configuration Summary. disabled(0)..........no Switch Configuration Summary.

snDhcpGatewayListTable.name: snDhcpGatewayListTable
snDhcpGatewayListTable.description: A table of DHCP gateway list of addresses.

snDhcpGatewayListEntry.name: snDhcpGatewayListEntry
snDhcpGatewayListEntry.description: An entry in the IP Port Address table.

snDhcpGatewayListId.name: snDhcpGatewayListId
snDhcpGatewayListId.description: The ID for a DHCP gateway list entry.

snDhcpGatewayListAddrList.name: snDhcpGatewayListAddrList
snDhcpGatewayListAddrList.description: The DHCP gateway address list for each DHCP gateway list ID. This list contains 1 to 8 IP addresses represented by octet string.

snDhcpGatewayListRowStatus.name: snDhcpGatewayListRowStatus
snDhcpGatewayListRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row or modifies an exsisting row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. Deleted rows go away immediately. The following values can be returned on reads: noSuch(0)...no such row other(1)....some other case valid(2)....the row exists and is valid

snDnsGatewayIpAddrList.name: snDnsGatewayIpAddrList
snDnsGatewayIpAddrList.description: The DNS Gateway IP address list. This list contains 4 IP addresses represented by octet string.

snMacFilterEntry.name: snMacFilterEntry
snMacFilterEntry.description: An entry in the MAC filter table.

snMacFilterIndex.name: snMacFilterIndex
snMacFilterIndex.description: The table index for a filter entry.

snMacFilterAction.name: snMacFilterAction
snMacFilterAction.description: Action to take if the Mac packet match with this filter.

snMacFilterFrameType.name: snMacFilterFrameType
snMacFilterFrameType.description: Frame Type: ethernet-type, LLC and SNAP types

snMacFilterRowStatus.name: snMacFilterRowStatus
snMacFilterRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row modify(5)...modifies an exsisting row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. Deleted rows go away immediately. The following values can be returned on reads: noSuch(0)...no such row invalid(1)...Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative.. valid(2)....the row exists and is valid

snMacFilterPortAccessEntry.name: snMacFilterPortAccessEntry
snMacFilterPortAccessEntry.description: An entry in the MAC Filter Port access table.

snMacFilterPortAccessPortIndex.name: snMacFilterPortAccessPortIndex
snMacFilterPortAccessPortIndex.description: The port index. For FastIron/NetIron products, port index value is from 1 to 42 For BigIron products, port index is an encoded number: The bit 0 to bit 7: port number. The bit 8 to bit 11: slot number. For virtual router interface, slot number is 15, port number is the virtual router port from 1 to 60. Therefore, port index value for BigIron is from 257 to 3900.

snMacFilterPortAccessFilters.name: snMacFilterPortAccessFilters
snMacFilterPortAccessFilters.description: 1st octet correspond to 1st filter number and so on.

snMacFilterPortAccessRowStatus.name: snMacFilterPortAccessRowStatus
snMacFilterPortAccessRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. Deleted rows go away immediately. The following values can be returned on reads: noSuch(0)...no such row invalid(1)...Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative.. valid(2)....the row exists and is valid

snNTPPollInterval.name: snNTPPollInterval
snNTPPollInterval.description: Interval specifies how often to poll the NTP server. Each unit is one second.

snNTPSummerTimeEnable.name: snNTPSummerTimeEnable
snNTPSummerTimeEnable.description: Enable/Disable daylight saving time. This enables daylight saving time for time/date starting 02:00:00 of first Sunday in April and ending 02:00:00 of last Sunday in October every year.

snNTPSystemClock.name: snNTPSystemClock
snNTPSystemClock.description: System clock, in the following format: octet 0: seconds after the minute [0-60] octet 1: minutes after the hour [0-59] octet 2: hours since midnight [0-23] octet 3: day of the month [1-31] octet 4: months since January [0-11] octet 5: years since 1900 octet 6: days since Sunday [0-6] Setting this object requires valid value in octets 0 to 5, and zero in octet 6. System clock can be disabled by setting zero to all octets.

snNTPSync.name: snNTPSync
snNTPSync.description: Initiate time synchronization to the NTP servers. For set operation, only 'synchronize(2)' is accepted. For get operation, always return 'other(1)'.

snNTPServerEntry.name: snNTPServerEntry
snNTPServerEntry.description: An entry in the NTP server table.

snNTPServerRowStatus.name: snNTPServerRowStatus
snNTPServerRowStatus.description: To create or delete a NTP server table entry.

snRadiusSNMPAccess.name: snRadiusSNMPAccess
snRadiusSNMPAccess.description: Indicate whether Radius group MIB obejcts can be accessed by SNMP manager. If value is disabled, all Radius group MIB objects return 'general error'.

snRadiusRetransmit.name: snRadiusRetransmit
snRadiusRetransmit.description: The number of authentication query retransmissions to the Radius server.

snRadiusTimeOut.name: snRadiusTimeOut
snRadiusTimeOut.description: Interval specifies how long to wait for authentication reply from the Radius server, each unit is one second.

snRadiusDeadTime.name: snRadiusDeadTime
snRadiusDeadTime.description: Interval specifies Radius server dead time, each unit is one minute.

snRadiusKey.name: snRadiusKey
snRadiusKey.description: Authentication key displayed as encrypted text.

snRadiusLoginMethod.name: snRadiusLoginMethod
snRadiusLoginMethod.description: A sequence of authentication methods. Each octet represents a method to authenticate the user login process. Each octet has the following enumeration value: enable(1) - authenticate by command line interface enable password radius(2) - authenticate by requesting radius server local(3) - authenticate by local user account table line(4) - authenticate by telnet password tacplus(5) - authenticate by requesting tacplus server none(6) - do not authenticate tacacs(7) - authenticate by requesting tacacs server Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous authentication methods.

snRadiusEnableMethod.name: snRadiusEnableMethod
snRadiusEnableMethod.description: A sequence of authentication methods. Each octet represents a method to authenticate the user entering priviledge mode of the command line interface. Each octet has the following enumeration value: enable(1) - authenticate by command line interface enable password radius(2) - authenticate by requesting radius server local(3) - authenticate by local user account table line(4) - authenticate by telnet password tacplus(5) - authenticate by requesting tacplus server none(6) - do not authenticate tacacs(7) - authenticate by requesting tacacs server Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous authentication methods.

snRadiusWebServerMethod.name: snRadiusWebServerMethod
snRadiusWebServerMethod.description: A sequence of authentication methods. Each octet represents a method to authenticate the user accessing the web-server. Each octet has the following enumeration value: enable(1) - authenticate by command line interface enable password radius(2) - authenticate by requesting radius server local(3) - authenticate by local user account table line(4) - authenticate by telnet password tacplus(5) - authenticate by requesting tacplus server none(6) - do not authenticate tacacs(7) - authenticate by requesting tacacs server Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous authentication methods.

snRadiusSNMPServerMethod.name: snRadiusSNMPServerMethod
snRadiusSNMPServerMethod.description: A sequence of authentication methods. Each octet represents a method to authenticate the user accessing the snmp-server. Each octet has the following enumeration value: enable(1) - authenticate by command line interface enable password radius(2) - authenticate by requesting radius server local(3) - authenticate by local user account table line(4) - authenticate by telnet password tacplus(5) - authenticate by requesting tacplus server none(6) - do not authenticate tacacs(7) - authenticate by requesting tacacs server Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous authentication methods.

snRadiusServerEntry.name: snRadiusServerEntry
snRadiusServerEntry.description: An entry in the Radius server table.

snRadiusServerRowStatus.name: snRadiusServerRowStatus
snRadiusServerRowStatus.description: To create or delete a Radius server table entry.

snRadiusServerRowKey.name: snRadiusServerRowKey
snRadiusServerRowKey.description: Authentication key displayed as encrypted text.

snRadiusServerUsage.name: snRadiusServerUsage
snRadiusServerUsage.description: To allow this server to be dedicated for a particular AAA activity.

snTacacsRetransmit.name: snTacacsRetransmit
snTacacsRetransmit.description: The number of authentication query retransmissions to the Tacacs server.

snTacacsTimeOut.name: snTacacsTimeOut
snTacacsTimeOut.description: Interval specifies how long to wait for authentication reply from the Tacacs server, each unit is one second.

snTacacsDeadTime.name: snTacacsDeadTime
snTacacsDeadTime.description: Interval specifies Tacacs server dead time, each unit is one minute.

snTacacsKey.name: snTacacsKey
snTacacsKey.description: Authentication key displayed as encrypted text.

snTacacsSNMPAccess.name: snTacacsSNMPAccess
snTacacsSNMPAccess.description: Indicate whether Tacacs group MIB obejcts can be accessed by SNMP manager. If value is disabled, all Tacacs group MIB objects return 'general error'.

snTacacsServerEntry.name: snTacacsServerEntry
snTacacsServerEntry.description: An entry in the Tacacs server table.

snTacacsServerRowStatus.name: snTacacsServerRowStatus
snTacacsServerRowStatus.description: To create or delete a Tacacs server table entry.

snTacacsServerRowKey.name: snTacacsServerRowKey
snTacacsServerRowKey.description: Authentication key displayed as encrypted text.

snTacacsServerUsage.name: snTacacsServerUsage
snTacacsServerUsage.description: To allow this server to be dedicated for a particular AAA activity.

snQosProfileTable.name: snQosProfileTable
snQosProfileTable.description: A table contains the configuration of qos profile groups.

snQosProfileIndex.name: snQosProfileIndex
snQosProfileIndex.description: The table index of QOS Profile.

snQosBindTable.name: snQosBindTable
snQosBindTable.description: A table contains the configuration of 802.1p to qos profile binding groups.

snQosBindIndex.name: snQosBindIndex
snQosBindIndex.description: The table index of QOS Bind.

snQosBindProfileIndex.name: snQosBindProfileIndex
snQosBindProfileIndex.description: QOS Bind Profile Index. This is pointer to the index of snQosProfile Table.

snAuthorizationCommandMethods.name: snAuthorizationCommandMethods
snAuthorizationCommandMethods.description: A sequence of authorization methods. Each octet represents a method to authorize the user command. Each octet has the following value: radius(2) - authorize by requesting radius server tacplus(5) - authorize by requesting tacplus server none(6) - skip authorization Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous authorization methods.

snAuthorizationCommandLevel.name: snAuthorizationCommandLevel
snAuthorizationCommandLevel.description: Commands, which are equal to and less than the specified command level here needs to be authorized. Possible enumeration values: 0 - Privilege level 0 4 - Privilege level 4 5 - Privilege level 5.

snAuthorizationExec.name: snAuthorizationExec
snAuthorizationExec.description: A sequence of exec authorization methods. Each octet represents a method for telnet or SSH login authorization. Each octet has the following enumeration value: radius(2) - send exec authorization request to radius server tacplus(5) - send exec authorization request to tacplus server none(6) - no exec authorization Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all authorization methods.

snAccountingCommandMethods.name: snAccountingCommandMethods
snAccountingCommandMethods.description: A sequence of accounting methods. Each octet represents a method to account for the user command. Each octet has the following enumeration value: radius(2) - send accounting info to radius server tacplus(5) - send accounting info to tacplus server none(6) - skip accounting Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous accounting methods.

snAccountingCommandLevel.name: snAccountingCommandLevel
snAccountingCommandLevel.description: Commands, which are equal to and less than the specified command level here will be accounted. Possible enumeration values: level0 - Privilege level 0 level4 - Privilege level 4 level5 - Privilege level 5.

snAccountingExec.name: snAccountingExec
snAccountingExec.description: A sequence of accounting methods. Each octet represents a method for telnet or SSH login accounting. Each octet has the following enumeration value: radius(2) - send accounting info to radius server tacplus(5) - send accounting info to tacplus server none(6) - skip accounting Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous accounting methods.

snAccountingSystem.name: snAccountingSystem
snAccountingSystem.description: A sequence of accounting methods. Each octet represents a method to account for the system related events. Each octet has the following enumeration value: radius(2) - send accounting info to radius server tacplus(5) - send accounting info to tacplus server none(6) - skip accounting Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous accounting methods.

snNetFlowGblProtocolDisable.name: snNetFlowGblProtocolDisable
snNetFlowGblProtocolDisable.description: bit 0 - other, disable all protocols export except UDP and TCP bit 1 - tcp, disable TCP protocol export bit 2 - udp, disable UDP protocol export

snNetFlowGblActiveTimeout.name: snNetFlowGblActiveTimeout
snNetFlowGblActiveTimeout.description: Maximum time an active flow can be in the NetFlow cache (minutes: 1..60)

snNetFlowGblInactiveTimeout.name: snNetFlowGblInactiveTimeout
snNetFlowGblInactiveTimeout.description: Maximum time an inactive flow can be in the NetFlow cache (seconds: 10..600)

snNetFlowCollectorTable.name: snNetFlowCollectorTable
snNetFlowCollectorTable.description: A table of each NetFlow collector information.

snNetFlowCollectorEntry.name: snNetFlowCollectorEntry
snNetFlowCollectorEntry.description: A row in the NetFlow collector table.

snNetFlowCollectorIndex.name: snNetFlowCollectorIndex
snNetFlowCollectorIndex.description: The index to the NetFlow collector table.

snNetFlowCollectorUdpPort.name: snNetFlowCollectorUdpPort
snNetFlowCollectorUdpPort.description: The NetFlow collector UDP port number.

snNetFlowCollectorSourceInterface.name: snNetFlowCollectorSourceInterface
snNetFlowCollectorSourceInterface.description: The ifIndex value to specify source port to export NetFlow packet. Value 0 to indicate default outgoing port.

snNetFlowCollectorRowStatus.name: snNetFlowCollectorRowStatus
snNetFlowCollectorRowStatus.description: To create or delete a NetFlow collector table entry.

snNetFlowAggregationTable.name: snNetFlowAggregationTable
snNetFlowAggregationTable.description: A table of each NetFlow aggregation scheme information.

snNetFlowAggregationEntry.name: snNetFlowAggregationEntry
snNetFlowAggregationEntry.description: A row in the NetFlow Aggregation table.

snNetFlowAggregationIp.name: snNetFlowAggregationIp
snNetFlowAggregationIp.description: The NetFlow aggregation collector ip address.

snNetFlowAggregationUdpPort.name: snNetFlowAggregationUdpPort
snNetFlowAggregationUdpPort.description: The NetFlow aggregation collector UDP port number.

snNetFlowAggregationSourceInterface.name: snNetFlowAggregationSourceInterface
snNetFlowAggregationSourceInterface.description: The ifIndex value to specify source port to export NetFlow aggregation packet. Value 0 to indicate default outgoing port.

snNetFlowAggregationNumberOfCacheEntries.name: snNetFlowAggregationNumberOfCacheEntries
snNetFlowAggregationNumberOfCacheEntries.description: Number of cache entries for aggregation scheme

snNetFlowAggregationActiveTimeout.name: snNetFlowAggregationActiveTimeout
snNetFlowAggregationActiveTimeout.description: Maximum time an active flow can be in the aggregation cache

snNetFlowAggregationInactiveTimeout.name: snNetFlowAggregationInactiveTimeout
snNetFlowAggregationInactiveTimeout.description: Maximum time an inactive flow can be in the aggregation cache

snNetFlowAggregationEnable.name: snNetFlowAggregationEnable
snNetFlowAggregationEnable.description: Enable/disable NetFlow aggregation for this aggregation scheme.

snNetFlowAggregationRowStatus.name: snNetFlowAggregationRowStatus
snNetFlowAggregationRowStatus.description: To create or delete a NetFlow collector table entry.

snNetFlowIfTable.name: snNetFlowIfTable
snNetFlowIfTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of ifNumber.

snNetFlowIfEntry.name: snNetFlowIfEntry
snNetFlowIfEntry.description: Entry containing the type of switching performed on that interface.

snNetFlowIfIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each interface. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each interface sub-layer must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

snNetFlowIfFlowSwitching.name: snNetFlowIfFlowSwitching
snNetFlowIfFlowSwitching.description: To enable/disable flow switching in a particular interface: disable (0) - no flow switching enable (1) - flow switching

snSflowCollectorTable.description: Table of all but first sFlow collectors. The first collector can be configured using sFlowTable in RFC 3176. The RFC cannot be used to configure more than one sFlow collectors. This table has been created to fill this gap.

snSflowCollectorEntry.description: A row in the sFlow collector table.

snSflowCollectorIndex.name: snSflowCollectorIndex
snSflowCollectorIndex.description: The index to the sFlow collector table.

snSflowCollectorUDPPort.name: snSflowCollectorUDPPort
snSflowCollectorUDPPort.description: The sFlow collector UDP port number.

snSflowCollectorRowStatus.description: To create, update or delete a SFlow collector table entry. If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. Deleted rows go away immediately. The following values can be returned on reads: noSuch(0)...no such row other(1)....some other case valid(2)....the row exists and is valid

snFdpInterfaceTable.name: snFdpInterfaceTable
snFdpInterfaceTable.description: Status of FDP on the device's interfaces.

snFdpInterfaceEntry.name: snFdpInterfaceEntry
snFdpInterfaceEntry.description: An entry in the snFdpInterfaceTable, having the status of FDP on an interface.

snFdpInterfaceIfIndex.name: snFdpInterfaceIfIndex
snFdpInterfaceIfIndex.description: ifIndex value of the local interface.

snFdpInterfaceFdpEnable.name: snFdpInterfaceFdpEnable
